properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 4 at 2:21PM CST until January 6 at 2:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...STRONG WINDS EXPECTED TO DEVELOP ACROSS LAKE MICHIGAN ON
SUNDAY...

* WHAT...South winds will increase to 15 to 20 knots with gusts to
25 knots Sunday morning. The south winds will turn to the west
and increase to gale force gusts to 35 knots and linger into
Sunday evening.  Waves building to 3 to 5 feet.

* WHERE...Nearshore waters from Sheboygan to Winthrop Harbor IL.

* WHEN...A Small Craft Advisory is in effect from 6 am to noon CST
Sunday. A Gale Warning is in effect from noon Sunday to 2 AM CST
Monday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO NOON CST SUNDAY... ...GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM NOON SUNDAY TO 2 AM CST MONDAY
